What is the output of the following algorithm?

arr = [64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90]
n = len(arr)
for i in range(n):
    for j in range(0, n-i-1):
        if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
            arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
print(arr)

What is the output of the following algorithm?

def find_max(arr):
    if not arr: return None
    max_val = arr[0]
    for val in arr:
        if val > max_val:
            max_val = val
    return max_val

print(find_max([3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6]))
